@model int

@{
    ViewData["Title"] = $"Lesson {Model}";
}

<div class="container lessQuizNum col-10">
    <h3 class="lessQuizNum">Lesson @Model</h3>
    <h1 class="lessName">The Importance of Learning Quantum Computing</h1><br />

    <div class="row">
        <div class="col-3">
            <img class="w-100 h-50 mt-5 rounded-3 border border-dark border-3" src="~/images/less3_Pic1.jpg" />
        </div>
        <div class="col-9 fs-5">
            <p>Quantum computing is an emerging field that holds significant potential for transforming the way we solve problems and process information. Here are some reasons why learning about quantum computing is important.</p>
            <h5 class="fw-bold opacity-75">Potential for Disruptive Impact</h5>
            If large-scale, fault-tolerant quantum computers become a reality, they could significantly impact various sectors, including cryptography, materials science, optimization, machine learning, and more. Understanding quantum computing allows individuals and organizations to prepare for these potential shifts.
            <br /><br />
            <h5 class="fw-bold opacity-75">Innovation and Research Opportunities</h5>
            As an active area of research, quantum computing offers many opportunities for contributing to new discoveries and innovations. Students, academics, and professionals with knowledge of quantum computing can contribute to this exciting field.
            <br /><br />
        </div>
    </div>

    <div class="row">
        <div class="col-3">
            <img class="w-100 h-50 mt-5 rounded-3 border border-dark border-3" src="~/images/less3_Security.jpg" />
        </div>
        <div class="col-9 fs-5">
            <h5 class="fw-bold opacity-75">Cryptography and Security</h5>
            Quantum computers could potentially break many current cryptographic systems. Understanding quantum computing is crucial for developing and implementing quantum-resistant cryptographic methods, which is important for maintaining security in a post-quantum world.
            <br /><br />
            <h5 class="fw-bold opacity-75">Interdisciplinary Nature</h5>
            Quantum computing lies at the intersection of physics, computer science, mathematics, and information theory. Learning about quantum computing can enrich your understanding of these fields and foster interdisciplinary thinking.
            <br /><br />
        </div>
    </div>

    <div class="row">
        <div class="col-3">
            <img class="w-100 h-50 mt-5 rounded-3 border border-dark border-3" src="~/images/less3_JobOpp.jpg" />
        </div>
        <div class="col-9 fs-5">
            <h5 class="fw-bold opacity-75">Job Opportunities</h5>
            As the field grows, so does the demand for quantum computing professionals. Learning about quantum computing can open up new career opportunities in academia, industry, and government.
            <br /><br />
            <h5 class="fw-bold opacity-75">Fundamental Understanding</h5>
            Quantum computing is based on principles of quantum mechanics, which are fundamental to our understanding of nature. Learning about quantum computing can help deepen your understanding of these underlying principles.
            <br /><hr />
            It's worth noting that while quantum computing holds great potential, it's still an emerging field, and many of its promises are currently theoretical. It's also a complex subject that requires understanding some advanced concepts in physics and mathematics. However, for those willing to delve into it, quantum computing can be a fascinating and rewarding area of study.
        </div>
    </div>

    @await Html.PartialAsync("_TakeQuizPrevNextButtons", Model)
</div>
